Chairman of the Caretaker/Extra-Ordinary National Convention Planning Committee (CENCPC) of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) Governor Mai Mala Buni on Tuesday said his committee has successfully resolved intra-party crisis in eleven states in the last three months. He disclosed this while inaugurating the party’s 12-man Reconciliation and Election Committee for Bayelsa Central and West Senatorial districts led by Gombe Governor Mohammad Yahaya. The Caretaker Committee Chairman, who was represented by his Secretary, Senator James Akpanndoedehe, said the committee has within the same period attracted to the party some highly placed members of the opposition. “Today, we proudly parade political heavy weights like the former Speaker of the House of Representatives Hon. Yakubu Dogara; Former PDP National chairman, Senator Barnabas Gemade; several members of the National Assembly, Chief Jimoh Ibrahim; former Head of Service of the Federation, Mr Danladi Kifasi; Sen. Isa Hamma Misau, Alhaji Salisu Takai and several others while, many others have also indicated interests to join the party.” Buni attributed the successes recorded to support the committee has been enjoying from stakeholders, adding the leadership of the party is committed to leading it away from unnecessary wrangling, squabbles and disputes. Yahaya said the committee would work assiduously to reconcile all the differences in the two senatorial districts of Bayelsa and ensure victory for the party at the poll on October 31. The committee members include Senator Ovie Omo-Agege – Vice Chairman; Senator Abdullahi Sahabi; Senator Ali Ndume; Senator Uba Sani; Ambassador Fatima Goni; Senator Chris Adegije; Alh Yusuf O. Ocholi; Chief Enyi o. Enyi; Pearl Ekebong Inwang and Bar. Ekemini Cletus Udoh to serve as Secretary